    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c7d80d46_6f2577e6",
        "filename": "client/annotation.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 61,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144624
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-13T22:33:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think Bruce\u0027s point on the design doc that we should have some limit is totally valid. Maybe 2k is too low, but for now I don\u0027t see why staying this low is a problem, especially given the SimpleStringDictionary limits. Since upping this at a later date can be done with no ill effect, is there a concern? I was actually wondering if this is something that should be #define\u0027able when building.",
      "parentUuid": "8eb0cacb_2b9ee450",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 61,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 61,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "8ea2b5e2f1f00ab7062a34d722909c4581c7dd93",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
