        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-13T18:26:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is going to be hard to use (without casts) since Type is an “enum class”. You can make that easier on clients by having the interface accept/return std::underlying_type\u003cType\u003e::type instead of Type.",
      "revId": "8ea2b5e2f1f00ab7062a34d722909c4581c7dd93",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
