      "writtenOn": "2017-10-13T22:33:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, that\u0027s something I had noticed in working with it a little. Even if we used underlying_type, constructing off of kUserDefinedStart still requires a cast. I took a different approach and added a constexpr helper to create a UserDefinedType().",
      "parentUuid": "3ff0859b_c15fd16a",
