        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-13T18:26:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can we separate the “value” operations out from the “key, value” operations? (I guess this would separate link_node_ and name_ into the owner object, and value_ptr_, size_, and type_ into the owned one.)\n\nRationale: with the flexibility we’re talking about, the “value” side of one of these may be useful in a non-“map” context. We may want to have simpler (array/sequence/vector) things, without the “name” stuff.",
      "revId": "8ea2b5e2f1f00ab7062a34d722909c4581c7dd93",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
